UNIMPOSSIBLE — file structure

  index.html            (root — open/serve this)
  manifest.json         (root — PWA app metadata)
  sw.js                 (root — service worker; MUST stay at root, see below)
  readme.txt            (this file)

  game/
    game.js             the engine
    styles.css          all styling
    words.json          the word list (3,703 words)
    dev.js              optional dev panel — DELETE for production

  images/
    icon-180.png        iOS home-screen icon
    icon-192.png        PWA icon
    icon-512.png        PWA icon / splash
    favicon-32.png      browser tab
    icon-unimpossible.svg   master artwork (keep for future edits)
    email-designasaur.png   contact image shown in the About modal


PATHS
  All paths are relative to index.html.
  game.js fetches the word list as 'game/words.json'.
  The About modal loads 'images/email-designasaur.png'.

  sw.js MUST stay at the site root. A service worker can only control pages at
  or below its own folder, so it could not cache index.html from a subfolder.


RUNNING IT
  Serve over http/https — NOT file:// — because the page fetches words.json.
  Locally:  python3 -m http.server     then open http://localhost:8000
  Service workers also require https (or localhost), so the PWA features only
  activate on a real host or localhost.


INSTALLING AS AN APP
  iOS:      Safari > Share > Add to Home Screen
  Android:  Chrome > menu > Install app / Add to Home Screen
  Desktop:  Chrome/Edge show an install icon in the address bar
  Launches fullscreen with the Unimpossible icon, and plays offline.


PRODUCTION CLEANUP
  - delete game/dev.js
  - remove the dev-panel markup and <script src="game/dev.js"> from index.html
  - bump CACHE = 'unimpossible-v1' in sw.js when deploying big changes
